    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offered here is an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 (FD3S) in concours-level condition. This example retains its factory-spec 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The chassis dynamics are preserved via the original double-wishbone suspension geometry and a perfectly balanced 50/50 weight distribution. Power is delivered through a crisp 5-speed manual transmission to a Torsen limited-slip differential. Every vacuum line, solenoid, and cooling component has been meticulously maintained to ensure peak thermal efficiency and boost response. This is a rare, unmodified specimen with a pristine undercarriage and flawless paint depth, representing the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering.",
